1) 
   The same functionality but for bourne shell, e.g.

   configure:
   MKC_CONFIG_MK=mkc_config.mk
   MKC_CONFIG_H=mkc_config.h

   MKC_CHECK_HEADERS='
      header1.h
      header2.h
      header3.h'
   MKC_CHECK_FUNCLIBS='
      func1:lib1
      func2
      func3:lib3'
   #<...>
   . mkc_configure
   mkc_run # generating mkc_config.h and mkc_config.mk

2) Adapt/test shell scripts for stupid/ancient Solaris' /bin/sh

3) MKC_REQD - user settable variable for specifing minimal required
   version of mk-configure

4) Adapt/test for pmake (old NetBSD make) already packaged for several
   Linux distros

5)
   MKC_NOAUTO_abcdefg...
